==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Myristic
<hw>My*ris"tic</hw> <pr>(m⟦icr⟧*r⟦icr⟧s"t⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or derived from, the nutmeg
(<gen>Myristica</gen>). Specifically, designating an acid
(<chform>C14H28O2</chform>) found in nutmeg oil and otoba fat, and
extracted as a white crystalline waxy substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Myristin</ent>⟦br⟧
